  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nWhen \"forge install\"-ing a repo which itself has contract dependencies it fetches npm (eg, openzeppelin libs), forge install does not recursively install the dependencies.\r\n\r\nInstead, you have to `cd lib/my-external-repo/` and then `npm install` \r\n\r\nWould be nice if forge install would do this for me, or maybe expose a flag for it\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
